title._content: ["Wellington," Malcolm Matheson house, Fox Hunt Road, Alexandria, Virginia. (LOC)

description._content: Johnston, Frances Benjamin,, 1864-1952,, photographer. ["Wellington," Malcolm Matheson house, Fox Hunt Road, Alexandria, Virginia. Porch] [1931] 1 photograph : glass lantern slide, hand-colored ; 3.25 x 4 in. Notes: Site History. Built in the 18th century for Colonel Tobias Lear; from his death in 1818, owned by descendents of George Washington. Today: Extant. On slide (handwritten): "Wellington" and no. "157." Also, typed name "Alexandria Garden Club." Title and date from Johnston's Carnegie Survey of the Architecture of the South, LC-J7-VA- 1699, with additional information provided by Sam Watters, 2011. Forms part of: Garden and historic house lecture series in the Frances Benjamin Johnston Collection (Library of Congress). Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication. Repository: Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division, Washington, D.C. 20540 USA, hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.print Higher resolution image is available (Persistent URL): hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ppmsca.16340 Call Number: LC-J717-X101- 40
